name: RealCartoon-Anime
description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy Coffee)

Please click "read more" to see more detail on the "why" for each version of this model.

**7/01/23: Added V3 Pruned.

...Please Share your images...Love seeing the results...

VAE is Baked in. ALL THE SAMPLES WERE RUN WITHOUT A VAE. MOST ON FULL VERSIONS.

The normal settings I ran it at are as follows:

  • Width: 512 (Have done up to 568)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 900)

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras/Eulaer A are the ones I use the most (Also DPM++ 2M Karras)

  • Sampling steps: 27-30 normally (27 is a nice spot for Euler A)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+ and 4k-UltraSharp), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (2)

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Ran ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but mainly if I was doing a DPM sampler

Why a new model?

This version of RealCartoon3D will focus more in the anime direction. Gives me another path to work towards. There is also RealCartoon-Realistic to bring more realism to the base model. I am hoping the RealCartoon3D version will keep that happy medium.

Why Anime?

Why not?

About Version 1

RealCartoon3D is the base, but I have been playing around with different merges and loras to try and get a nice anime look. I hope you enjoy!

About Version 2

This version is much smoother in the art style. Version 1 is more dark edge. Also, this one seems to handle hands better than V1. Overall, I have been enjoying the results from this one. SAMPLES FOR THIS ONE DID NOT HAVE ADetailer running.

About Version 3

This version gets some nice results with the prompts. This one took a bit to get the look and keep the versatility of the checkpoint. Overall, I like it. I hope you all do as well. Please rate and share your images!!
